[h1]Phobos' Industrial Pathways: Biomass[/h1]

[b]Version:[/b] 1.11.1 | [b]Requires:[/b] Project Zomboid Build 42.14.0+ | [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3668598865]PhobosLib 1.30.0+[/url] | [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3615135168]Zombie Virus Vaccine[/url]

A complete industrial chemistry and biomass processing suite for Project Zomboid Build 42. 301 recipes, 120 items, 10 fluids, 66 sandbox options. Realistic crafting pathways for blackpowder, biodiesel, soap, bone char, salt, agriculture, recycling, hemp, horticulture, and lab processes.

[i]Part of the Phobos' Industrial Pathways mod series.[/i]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]Features[/h2]

[h3]Applied Chemistry Skill[/h3]
Custom perk with steep XP curve (75-9000), 7 skill tiers, 5 skill books, 2 occupations (Chemist, Pharmacist), and 2 traits. All recipes award Applied Chemistry XP.

[h3]Blackpowder Pathway[/h3]
Seven-step chain from raw charcoal to gunpowder: crush, purify, compost, extract battery acid, extract sulphur, synthesize potassium nitrate, mix blackpowder.

[h3]Biodiesel & Fat Rendering[/h3]
Extract oil from 6 crops using 3 equipment tiers, transesterify with methanol and catalyst, wash, and refine into vehicle fuel. Render lard/butter/margarine or slow-cook butchered meat into biodiesel feedstock.

[h3]Soap, Bone Char & Salt[/h3]
Two soap pathways: glycerol-based from biodiesel by-products and fat-based from rendered fats. Pyrolyse bones for bone char filtration. Six-step salt extraction from water wells through brine concentration, crystallization, and purification.

[h3]Recycling Pathway[/h3]
Nine-step chain: wood tar to glue/torches, calcite to quicklime/fertilizer, crude soap to bars/bandages, lead to fishing tackle, plastic to glue, electronics to precision components.

[h3]Agriculture & Applications[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]Garden Sprays[/b] — Craft vanilla gardening sprays from chemistry intermediates
[*] [b]Mineral Feed[/b] — Bone char-based animal feed
[*] [b]Water Purification[/b] — Charcoal filters, purification tablets, gas mask recharging
[*] [b]Epoxy Resin[/b] — From wood tar and glycerol
[*] [b]Fire-Starting[/b] — Lighter fluid, matchboxes, slug repellent
[*] [b]Chemical Processing[/b] — Leather tanning, plaster, wood vinegar
[/list]

[h3]Botanical Pathway[/h3]
Hemp processing: chemical retting, fiber/hurd splitting into textiles (twine, rope, cloth, canvas, sack, sheet rope), papermaking, medicinals, fishing net, snare, oakum, and hurd products (charcoal, hempcrete, compost). Vanilla stations: Scutching Board, Loom, Hand Press. Cross-links to blackpowder, biodiesel, and construction. Sandbox-gated.

[h3]Horticulture[/h3]
45 items: tobacco (wet leaves, dual-path chewing tobacco via fire-cure or jar fermentation), hemp buds (fresh, cured, decarbed, canned, loose pouch), papermaking tools, smoking products (pipes, cigars, cigarettes, packs), edibles (hemp butter, hemp-infused oil), sugar syrup. Fermentation progress shown via dynamic tooltip.

[h3]Medicinal & Hemp Effects[/h3]
Poultice and tincture with timed actions, visual/audio feedback, and Medicated moodle (requires Moodle Framework). Hemp effects fully configurable via 33 sandbox options covering pipes, cigars, cigarettes, buds, poultice, tincture, and sugar syrup.

[h3]Concrete Mixer[/h3]
Powered CraftBench entity built from metal drum, salvaged motor, and welding equipment. Requires electricity. 13 recipes including concrete, mortar, reinforced concrete, and bulk chemistry. Generator fuel drain during crafting.

[h3]Recipe Books[/h3]
Six lootable books by category plus one master compendium:
[list]
[*] [b]Field Chemistry Primer[/b] — Blackpowder, recycling, agriculture
[*] [b]Kitchen Chemistry Companion[/b] — Fat rendering, soap, biodiesel, cooking
[*] [b]Laboratory Chemistry Reference[/b] — Lab processes, salt extraction
[*] [b]Industrial Processes Manual[/b] — Concrete mixer, bulk processing
[*] [b]Botanical Horticulture Guide[/b] — Hemp, textiles, horticulture
[*] [b]Complete Chemistry Compendium[/b] — All PCP recipes
[/list]

[h3]Advanced Lab Equipment[/h3]
Centrifuge, chromatograph, microscope, and spectrometer recipes. Microscope and spectrometer gated by sandbox option.

[h3]In-Game Guide & Changelog[/h3]
Welcome guide on first install. Version-based changelog popup on updates.

[hr][/hr]

[h2]Optional Systems[/h2]

[h3]Impurity/Purity System[/h3]
Condition-based purity tracking (0-100%) through recipe chains. Multiplicative skill influence (up to +44% at Level 10), ±15% variance, five yield tiers, equipment quality factors, and player feedback via speech bubbles and tooltips. Yield only penalises PCP multi-output recipes — vanilla outputs are always at full quantity.

[h3]Health Hazard System[/h3]
11 dangerous recipes split into Protected (mask + goggles, filter degradation) and Unprotected (disease/stat penalty risk) variants. EHR integration when available.

[h3]Vessel Replacement[/h3]
Empty PCP FluidContainers revert to vanilla vessels (mason jar + lid, bottle, bucket, gas can) on container open. MP-synced.

[h3]Tiered Reset/Cleanup[/h3]
Six one-shot sandbox options for version upgrades, migration, and mod removal. Each auto-resets to OFF after execution.

[hr][/hr]

[h2]Sandbox Options[/h2]
66 options: Yield Multiplier, Advanced Lab Recipes, Heat Sources, Impurity System (enable, severity, skill influence), Health Hazards, Botanical Pathway, Vessel Replacement, Concrete Mixer, Hemp Effects (33 per-product stat knobs), Horticulture Migration, Maintenance/Reset (6 one-shot options), Debug Logging.

[hr][/hr]

[h2]Cross-Mod Integration[/h2]
[list]
[*] [b]ZScienceSkill[/b] ("Science, Bitch!") — Applied Chemistry XP mirrors to Science at 50% rate; 91 items + 8 fluids registered as microscope specimens
[*] [b]EHR[/b] (Extensive Health Rework) — Health hazard recipes dispatch EHR diseases instead of vanilla stat penalties
[*] [b]Dynamic Trading[/b] — 73 PCP items registered for NPC trading with custom "Chemical" tag and "Chemist" trader archetype; chemical allocations injected into 8 existing vendor archetypes
[*] [b]Neat Crafting[/b] — Recipe visibility filters applied through NC_FilterBar; runtime-detected, no hard dependency
[*] [b]Moodle Framework[/b] — Medicinal items trigger a Medicated custom moodle with configurable duration; graceful no-op when not installed
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

